reviews.author_name: EpicurusHongKong Best Food of Hong Kong & Macau
reviews.text:
The multiple years Michelin recommended Cafe Malacca in Hong Kong ~ serves super authentic Malaysian & Singapore food.  This is to be expected since Hotel Jen here is also under the umbrella of Shangri-La and Kerry Group, which is Malaysian owned and they have utmost expectations and pride in this regard with pedigree.  

Signature dishes are many, but start with their Satay sticks, also Chwee Kueh dumplings which are rare to find.  The slightly sour Assam Laksa made with Mackerel dish here is also authentically done since the Executive Chef here is a Malaysian lady with plenty of passion and experience, earning her the Michelin recommendation.  Finish off with their accurate Ice Kacang dessert, Chendol or Durian items when it is in season during Summer time, ripened fruit off the trees then imported.  Amazing stuff..
Simple decor, bright and spacious.  For afternoon tea, choice of Western and Malaysian cuisine.
Pricey, but the food is wonderful - the best Malaysian food I've found in HK. Great beer, too.
The Mala dishes here is so good!

reviews.text: Very satisfied with this hotel, good location and good service. Everything is fine, only the pool is a bit too small. A surprise fruit tart from Hotel Jen, prepared a birthday card for my mother! It feels so warm and happy. In general, the value and fun there is worth it.

The location of the hotel is fantastic.
Our room was clean, included everything we needed for our stay.
The staff were all very helpful with transport needs, sightseeing recommendations and general information locally and across Hong Kong overall.
Gucci was fantastic and deserves an award for taking care of all of our needs, thank you team.

Super cool place. Friendly staff. Modern rooms. Clean. Great shower. Good views. Right next to the subway if you take exit B2 at HKU station. If you take any of the C exits you have to walk a thousand stairs. :D

We highly enjoyed our stay at Hotel Jen. The place is nice, clean, spacious, well organized. Service was great, very attentive and helpful.
Rooms were spacious, clean, and comfortable.
A great point is that the hotel is close to a metro station (HKU exit B2), which helps connect you to the entire city.
There are a few restaurants, shops, bars and cafes walking distance, but not a big tourist locale.
I would definitely recommend this hotel.

The central area is perfect 1 min away from the subway. Not told about the Jade level benefits on arrival. Also not upgraded on arrival. English was a language barrier for the person in the reception. But friendly and nice. Upscale hotel. Well worth the money.

reviews.text:
홍콩섬 내 가장 가성비 좋은 호텔..홍콩내 보편적 비즈 호텔들이 20제곱미터가 안되는데 여긴 일단 24제곱미터..일단 다른 홍콩호텔처럼 매우 좁다는 생각은 안든다. 지하철 홍콩대학에서 매우 가까워 홍콩역, 완차이 등 접근성이 뛰어나며 홍콩 국제공항간  a10버스를 이용할수 있다.  은근 맛집들이 주변에 많다. 케네디타운에 위치한 신흥식가도 해변길따라 도보로 다녀올 수 있는 거리..

옥상 수영장이 있으나 작으며 오후 7시30분까지만 오픈된다  결국 한번도 이용 못하고 구경만 함. ㅠㅠ 같은층 클럽라운지가 있음.

주변에 편의점 마켓 sc은행 빵집 빠 맥도널드 해안가 등이 있으므로 편의적인 측면도 빠지지는 않는다. 

낮은층은 옆 건물들에서 보이므로 프라이버시를 위해..전망을 위해 가급적 고층에 투숙하기를 추천한다.

사진은 호텔 1층에서의 부근 모습

Very satisfied with this hotel, good location and good service. Everything is fine, only the pool is a bit too small. A surprise fruit tart from Hotel Jen, prepared a birthday card for my mother! It feels so warm and happy. In general, the value and fun there is worth it.

在香港的時間，一如既往喜愛Hotel Jen帶來的旅居體驗。

我們期待：床鋪再乾爽一些就會更棒喔，枕頭的選擇上選擇柔軟而富有支撐度的話睡眠質量會更好呢，另外棉拖鞋的纖維總是會黏腳板，選品質素也期待提高呢！

早餐方面，我們是很喜歡在Hotel Jen的餐廳用餐的，食物非常可口舒服。我們考慮的是，如果餐廳空氣（特別是靠近取食物和廚房的位置）空氣流通和清新度能做得更好，客人們的體驗印象應該會加分唷！

最後，我們很欣賞Hotel Jen同事們的熱忱和幫助。如果前台同事制服的選擇上可以更加得體、清潔和整齊（這一點在我以往的評價中也有提及），我們會覺得更加專業和欣賞呢！

謝謝 Hotel Jen總為我的香港旅行帶來非常棒的體驗，我們會繼續選擇入住呢，也期待酒店變得更好。
